net.ttddyy.dsproxy.proxy

Class CachedRowSetResultSetProxyLogic

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.ttddyy.dsproxy.proxy.ProxyLogicSupport
      • net.ttddyy.dsproxy.proxy.CachedRowSetResultSetProxyLogic
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ResultSetProxyLogic

    public class CachedRowSetResultSetProxyLogic
extends ProxyLogicSupport
implements ResultSetProxyLogic
    Uses CachedRowSet to provide repeatable read ResultSet proxy. CachedRowSet is disconnected scrollable RowSet which is a subset of ResultSet. Using those feature to provide repeatable read resultset proxy. The default oracle jdk implementation com.sun.rowset.CachedRowSetImpl does not support isClosed method. Thus, keep close status and return it when isClosed() is called.
    Since:
    1.4.7
    Author:
    Tadaya Tsuyukubo
    See Also:
